profile_short_name:Catimor NAT Yunnan v1
profile_designer:Claude
profile_description:Yunnan Pu'er Catimor Natural 1650m\vMoisture: 11.5% | Density: 759g/L\vSuggested load: 60g\v\vVersion 1 - Initial profile for light roast exploration\v\vBean characteristics:\v- Low density (759g/L) = porous structure, fast heat transfer\v- Higher moisture (11.5%) needs adequate drying\v- Catimor variety (Robusta hybrid) - light roast preserves\v  floral/fruit notes and minimizes bitterness\v- 60g batch = half standard load, all parameters adjusted\v\vDesign philosophy:\v- Gentle approach: lower preheat (720W) to prevent tipping\v  on low-density beans with 60g small batch\v- Moderate mid-section slope for even Maillard development\v- Quick cooldown to lock in light roast character\v- Conservative expect_fc at 200C (lower density may crack earlier)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Nordic Light: Level 1.0 (~196C, ~10-12% dev)\v  Clean & Bright: Level 1.5 (~198C, ~13-15% dev)\v  Sweet & Balanced: Level 2.0 (~200C, ~16-18% dev)\v  Full Development: Level 2.5 (~202C, ~19-21% dev)\v\vTarget for first roast: Level 2.0 (explore natural flavors)\vExpected total time: 5:50-6:20\v\vSafety: No zone boosts, standard end_ratio/min_ROR.\vBased on SeanBrews F-NAT 1500-2200m template,\vadjusted for 60g load and Catimor characteristics.\v
